context: Valencia's port is the biggest on the <a1_0>Mediterranean western coast<a1_0/>, the first of Spain in container traffic as of 2008 and the <a2_0>second<a2_0/> of Spain in total traffic, handling <a0_0>20<a0_0/>% of Spain's exports. The main exports are foodstuffs and beverages. Other exports include <a3_0>oranges<a3_0/>, furniture, ceramic tiles, fans, textiles and iron products. Valencia's manufacturing sector focuses on metallurgy, chemicals, textiles, shipbuilding and brewing. Small and medium-sized industries are an important part of the local economy, and before the current crisis unemployment was lower than the Spanish average.
